How do I answer the man ?
#HINT#
2

#TEXT#
It is possible to answer either way, although you must be careful.
#FINISH#
#HINT#
2

#TEXT#
If he thinks you are lying, it will raise his level of suspicion, regardless of what
you said.
#FINISH#
#HINT#
2

#TEXT#
Also, the admission that you have seen the American agent is enough to generate
a little suspicion.
#FINISH#
#TOPIC#
1
Why doesn´t he believe my answer ?
#HINT#
6

#TEXT#
Is there any reason the man might KNOW that you've seen the American agent? 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
6

#TEXT#
Might the agent have left something behind, besides the document and the 
carnation?
#FINISH#
#HINT#
6

#TEXT#
Wasn't he holding his left arm? Mightn't it have been wounded?
#FINISH#
#HINT#
6

#TEXT#
LOOK AT THE FLOOR to see the blood that he's left here. It's a dead giveaway, 
no pun intended. It would be best to clean up after him.
#FINISH#
#HINT#
6

#TEXT#
In the lavatory, across the hall and to the south, there is a towel. Get it, wet it, then 
use it to clean up the blood.
#FINISH#
#HINT#
6

#TEXT#
Also, answering in a way that contradicts the evidence (i.e. the bloodiness of the 
floor), adds suspicion.
#FINISH#
