The Assassination
#TOPIC#
151
Where is the sniper hiding?
#HINT#
152

#TEXT#
Have you seen your contact, the antique dealer? 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
152

#TEXT#
The antique shop is just west of the southwest corner of the square (i.e. south and 
west of your starting position).
#FINISH#
#HINT#
152

#TEXT#
Be careful; the police are sometimes inside, checking around. They know who 
you are, so you'd better not get seen. 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
152

#TEXT#
You'll have to find out yourself on which floor of the apartment building the sniper 
is hiding, but at least your contact had the password. 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
152

#TEXT#
Perhaps he is, in some way, visible from the street; the town square might be a 
good vantage point. 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
152

#TEXT#
From the town square, try LOOKing AT THE WINDOWS or BUILDINGS. There 
are three open windows in the apartment building; the sniper is in one of them. 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
152

#TEXT#
In the apartment building's lobby, there is a directory of residents; maybe there is 
some information there. 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
152

#TEXT#
There is only one vacant apartment with the window open. Guess who's in it? 
#FINISH#
#TOPIC#
151
How do I get TO the sniper?
#HINT#
161

#TEXT#
You can try using the elevator in the apartment lobby.
#FINISH#
#HINT#
161

#TEXT#
Or, have you been into the alley?
#FINISH#
#HINT#
161

#TEXT#
Down at the end is a fire-escape ladder.
#FINISH#
#HINT#
161

#TEXT#
If you TAKE THE TRASH CAN, then PUT THE TRASH CAN UNDER THE 
LADDER, then STAND ON THE CAN, you can easily reach the ladder. Then, go 
up to the proper floor. 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
161

#TEXT#
Knock on the door, and have the password handy. If you don't give the password 
quickly, the sniper will ignore you for the remainder of the scenario. 
#FINISH#
#TOPIC#
151
How do I get the password?
#HINT#
167

#TEXT#
You'll have to meet with your contact, the antique dealer. See the previous 
question. 
#FINISH#
#TOPIC#
151
Should I kill the sniper?
#HINT#
169

#TEXT#
An interesting dilemma. If you kill the sniper, your cover is broken, due to suspicion 
regarding the gun used (yours) and the incident on the train, in which you lost the 
coded document. On the other hand, you stop the assassination. All in all, a mixed 
bag. You can do better. 
#FINISH#
#TOPIC#
151
Why does the sniper kill me?
#HINT#
171

#TEXT#
A variety of reasons. First, anything you do that might cause him to think you're 
intent on defeating him will get you killed. Also, arriving at his door while you're 
being pursued is a definite killer. 
#FINISH#
#TOPIC#
151
How can I avoid Topaz?
#HINT#
173

#TEXT#
Once he's seen you, he will doggedly pursue you for the remainder of your alloted 
time (i.e. until the assassination happens.) 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
173

#TEXT#
He can be avoided by staying away from the cafe. The more you pass by there or 
spend time there, the more likely that he'll see you. 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
173

#TEXT#
Maybe you don't want to avoid him... 
#FINISH#
#TOPIC#
151
Can Topaz help me?
#HINT#
177

#TEXT#
Firstly, his interest and yours are similar - preventing the assassination. In your 
case, however, you daren't risk exposing yourself to Topaz, firstly, for fear of being 
seen by other Soviet agents and, secondly, for fear of being killed by Topaz, who 
has an axe to grind with you. 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
177

#TEXT#
Can you arrange for Topaz to kill the sniper? 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
177

#TEXT#
Think about it... 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
177

#TEXT#
Topaz will follow you anywhere, even to the sniper's room. 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
177

#TEXT#
If you can lead him there, you're home free. Almost. 
#FINISH#
#TOPIC#
151
Topaz always catches me. Why?
#HINT#
183

#TEXT#
He's about the same speed as you, so you're usually fine. Unless you're in the 
alley, trying to get to the fire-escape ladder. That takes more time than you've got. 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
183

#TEXT#
Can you put a stumbling block in his way? 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
183

#TEXT#
You can TOPPLE THE VENDOR'S CART and make an unholy mess; that will 
hold Topaz for a little while. After that, it's up to you. 
#FINISH#
#TOPIC#
151
I can't get the best ending. Why?
#HINT#
187

#TEXT#
Presumably, you have found the sniper and know the password. 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
187

#TEXT#
Also, you know that Topaz can be made to kill the sniper for you. 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
187

#TEXT#
Meaning that Topaz must follow you up to the sniper's room. See the previous 
clue for help in this regard.
#FINISH#
#HINT#
187

#TEXT#
Once you're in the sniper's room, Topaz will never find you in time unless you've 
helped him along. 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
187

#TEXT#
DROP something before giving the password; it's presence will alert Topaz to 
yours. Oh, and make it small or the sniper will find it instead. 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
187

#TEXT#
And HIDE or STAND BEHIND THE DOOR so that you won't get in Topaz's line of 
fire and get killed with the sniper. 
#FINISH#
#HINT#
187

#TEXT#
Then, HIT TOPAZ, and he'll never know what happened. 
#FINISH#
